# Eval case: epfo-nps-fetcher

IDEA="Create a local desktop application for fetching EPFO and NPS data from the government portals (EPFO UAN member portal and NPS CRA) given the user's credentials. Automate login, scrape the passbook and statement of transactions, normalize them into a unified local store, and present a consolidated retirement-savings dashboard with contribution history and interest accrued. Credentials and data never leave the machine."

CONTEXT="Target: single Indian salaried user, laptop-only, no cloud sync, runs locally. Stack: Python; Playwright (headless browser automation); SQLite (encrypted via SQLCipher); Typer CLI; keyring for credential storage. Formats: EPFO UAN passbook; NPS CRA transaction statement. Limits: max 2 government sources; 1 user profile. Non-goals: cloud sync; storing credentials in plaintext; auto-investing; tax filing; multi-user; mobile app; React UI; selling or transmitting data to third parties. Defer: scheduled background sync; 2FA auto-handling; aggregator account APIs."
